  "body": "I think that we're seeing our nodes fall behind because we fail to download a block:\n`Failed to download block 0x913cfde20a088a30b32ed313d811a975ac9477ad1a0835a1bbcaf6517977f912 from peer Peer 0x793d60b925e42f06b3....`\nAnd then our retrying mechanism tries the same peer over and over, constantly failing. We then accumulate a list of announced blocks like so:\n```\nSaving announced block 12691323 (0x9f83e25f641f284548d10190711ce76adb2fb0ed389d14f2dc935282f66bc3e7) for future import\nFailed to download block 0x9f83e25f641f284548d10190711ce76adb2fb0ed389d14f2dc935282f66bc3e7 from peer Peer 0xb4ef50d23017563df3....\nImported 1 pending blocks\nImported #12,691,314 / 218 tx / 0 om / 14,984,326 (99.9%) gas / (0xfe8d96590862a1fb97db3c9e87b279142367eb0aadbfec39a2a324f4acd8285a) in 10.983s. Peers: 25\n```\nHere we see that we just imported block ...314 but we have blocks up to block ...323 saved.",
